<subSubSection id="C32E65595C06FFA248A6FF48FB49FF28" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B36D25C06FFA248A6FF48FB49FF28" blockId="25.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C06FFA248A6FF48FEF5FF4D" bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515C06FFA24ACCFF47FCD0FF4D" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1906" box="[685,798,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C06FFA24ACCFF47FCD0FF4D" box="[685,798,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">A. aeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only by having the pronotal disc without a transverse pronotal carina, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515C06FFA249D1FF63FDD3FF29" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1906" box="[432,541,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C06FFA249D1FF63FDD3FF29" box="[432,541,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">A. aeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the pronotal disc with a transverse pronotal carina.
</paragraph>
